  "rationale": "<p>Choice D is correct. A function defined by an equation in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals a left parenthesis b right parenthesis Superscript x plus h\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><msup><mfenced><mi>b</mi></mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>h</mi></mrow></msup></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\"><mi>a</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\"><mi>b</mi></math>, and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"h\"><mi>h</mi></math> are positive constants and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x greater than or equals 0\"><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8805;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>, has a minimum value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f left parenthesis 0 right parenthesis\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></math>. It's given that function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"g\"><mi>g</mi></math> is defined by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"g left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 18 left parenthesis 1.16 right parenthesis left parenthesis 1.4 right parenthesis Superscript x plus 2\"><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>18</mn><mfenced><mn>1.16</mn></mfenced><msup><mfenced><mn>1.4</mn></mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>, which is equivalent to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"g left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals 20.88 left parenthesis 1.4 right parenthesis Superscript x plus 2\"><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>20.88</mn><msup><mfenced><mn>1.4</mn></mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>. Substituting <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0\"><mn>0</mn></math> for <math xmlns=\"ht